SIMPLE: nihilist
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nihilist
<hw>Ni"hil*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>nihiliste</ets>.
See <er>Nihilism</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who advocates the
doctrine of nihilism; one who believes or teaches that nothing can be
known, or asserted to exist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Politics)</fld> <def>A member of a secret
association (esp. in Russia), which is devoted to the destruction of the
present political, religious, and social institutions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nihilistic</ent>⟦br⟧
